Absolute Forgiveness

	Philosophy

		-
			Absolute forgiveness is to vow not to hold the misdeeds and inadequacies of oneself or
			others against them personally, and to love them unconditionally.
		-

	Principles

		The Irrelevancy Principle

			-
				If a past event had no consequences that have persisted unto the present, save for
				any lingering emotions associated with it, it is irrelevant.
			-